.TH "copy_to_user_nofault" 9 "copy_to_user_nofault" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
copy_to_user_nofault \- safely attempt to write to a user-space location
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" copy_to_user_nofault
.BI "(void __user *dst "  ","
.BI "const void *src "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
address to write to
.IP "src" 12
pointer to the data that shall be written
.IP "size" 12
size of the data chunk
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Safely write to address \fIdst\fP from the buffer at \fIsrc\fP.  If a kernel fault
happens, handle that and return -EFAULT.
